                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/ecse-457" class="program-course-title">
              ECSE 457 ECSE Design Project 2 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22676" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Electrical &amp; Computer Engr (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Electrical Engineering              : A design project undertaken with close mentorship by a staff member and under the supervision of the course instructor. The course is a continuation of ECSE 456.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Michael Rabbat, Fabrice Labeau (Fall)                  Michael Rabbat, Fabrice Labeau (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisite: ECSE 456</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
